  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What Is Elicitation?"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "MCP elicitation is a mechanism that allows a server to pause a tool call mid-execution and ask the human operator a question. The server sends an elicitation request to the host, which renders a UI form for the human to fill in, and then the server receives the answer and continues."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This is fundamentally different from asking the model to gather more information \u2014 the model never sees the exchange. The conversation stays clean while the tool gets exactly what it needs from the person who knows the answer."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Not conversational turns: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "the model is blocked, waiting for the tool to return. No extra messages appear in the chat."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Human-in-the-loop without a round-trip: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "structured input collected inside the same tool invocation."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Host-mediated: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "the host application is responsible for rendering the form; the server just describes the schema."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Protocol Exchange"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Elicitation is defined in the MCP specification as a server-initiated notification/request pair. The flow at the JSON-RPC level looks like this:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "json"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# 1. Server sends elicitation/create\n{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"method\": \"elicitation/create\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"requestedSchema\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"confirm\": {\n          \"type\": \"boolean\",\n          \"title\": \"Confirm deletion\",\n          \"description\": \"Delete all 47 matching records?\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"required\": [\"confirm\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n# 2. Host shows a UI form to the human.\n#    Human clicks Yes or No.\n\n# 3. Host responds with the human's answer\n{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"result\": {\n    \"action\": \"accept\",\n    \"content\": {\n      \"confirm\": true\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n# 4. Server continues execution with confirm=True"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The response action field has three values:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "\"accept\" \u2014 the human submitted the form. content holds the values."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "\"decline\" \u2014 the human explicitly rejected the request."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "\"cancel\" \u2014 the host could not show the form (unsupported, timed out, etc.)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Elicitation flow: normal tool call vs elicitation with human pause"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Server-Side: Using Elicitation in Python"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The MCP Python SDK exposes elicitation through the request context. The session object gained a .elicit() method that wraps the protocol exchange:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from mcp.server import Server\nfrom mcp.server.stdio import stdio_server\nfrom mcp import types\n\napp = Server(\"file-manager\")\n\n@app.list_tools()\nasync def list_tools() -> list[types.Tool]:\n    return [\n        types.Tool(\n            name=\"delete_records\",\n            description=\"Delete database records matching a filter\",\n            inputSchema={\n                \"type\": \"object\",\n                \"properties\": {\n                    \"filter\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"description\": \"SQL WHERE clause\"},\n                    \"table\": {\"type\": \"string\"}\n                },\n                \"required\": [\"filter\", \"table\"]\n            }\n        )\n    ]\n\n@app.call_tool()\nasync def call_tool(name: str, arguments: dict):\n    if name != \"delete_records\":\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unknown tool: {name}\")\n\n    table = arguments[\"table\"]\n    filter_clause = arguments[\"filter\"]\n\n    # Count matches first\n    count = await db_count(table, filter_clause)\n\n    # Elicit confirmation from the human\n    ctx = app.request_context\n    result = await ctx.session.elicit(\n        message=f\"About to delete {count} records from {table}\",\n        requestedSchema={\n            \"type\": \"object\",\n            \"properties\": {\n                \"confirm\": {\n                    \"type\": \"boolean\",\n                    \"title\": \"Confirm deletion\",\n                    \"description\": f\"Delete all {count} matching records from {table}?\"\n                }\n            },\n            \"required\": [\"confirm\"]\n        }\n    )\n\n    if result.action != \"accept\" or not result.content.get(\"confirm\"):\n        return [types.TextContent(type=\"text\", text=\"Deletion cancelled by user.\")]\n\n    deleted = await db_delete(table, filter_clause)\n    return [types.TextContent(type=\"text\", text=f\"Deleted {deleted} records.\")]\n\nasync def main():\n    async with stdio_server() as (read, write):\n        await app.run(read, write, app.create_initialization_options())\n\nimport asyncio\nasyncio.run(main())"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Collecting a Secret at Runtime"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "One of the most valuable uses of elicitation is collecting a password or one-time code without the model ever seeing it:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "@app.call_tool()\nasync def call_tool(name: str, arguments: dict):\n    if name != \"connect_to_service\":\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unknown tool: {name}\")\n\n    service = arguments[\"service\"]\n    ctx = app.request_context\n\n    # Ask the human for their 2FA code\n    result = await ctx.session.elicit(\n        message=f\"2FA required for {service}\",\n        requestedSchema={\n            \"type\": \"object\",\n            \"properties\": {\n                \"otp\": {\n                    \"type\": \"string\",\n                    \"title\": \"One-time code\",\n                    \"description\": f\"Enter the 6-digit code from your authenticator app for {service}\",\n                    \"minLength\": 6,\n                    \"maxLength\": 6,\n                    \"pattern\": \"^[0-9]{6}$\"\n                }\n            },\n            \"required\": [\"otp\"]\n        }\n    )\n\n    if result.action != \"accept\":\n        return [types.TextContent(type=\"text\", text=\"Authentication cancelled.\")]\n\n    otp = result.content[\"otp\"]  # Never logged or sent to model\n    connection = await authenticate(service, otp)\n    return [types.TextContent(type=\"text\", text=f\"Connected to {service}.\")]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Security note: the OTP value travels server \u2192 host \u2192 human \u2192 host \u2192 server. The model running the tool call never sees it. Ensure your server discards the value immediately after use and never logs it."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Checking Elicitation Capability"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Elicitation requires explicit support from the host. A stdio-based local server connecting to Claude Desktop may find elicitation available; a remote HTTP+SSE server connecting to a headless agent may not. Always check the capability before calling .elicit():"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from mcp.server import Server\nfrom mcp import types\n\napp = Server(\"safe-server\")\n\n@app.call_tool()\nasync def call_tool(name: str, arguments: dict):\n    ctx = app.request_context\n    init_result = ctx.session.client_params\n\n    # Check if the client advertised elicitation support\n    client_caps = getattr(init_result, \"capabilities\", None)\n    has_elicitation = (\n        client_caps is not None\n        and getattr(client_caps, \"elicitation\", None) is not None\n    )\n\n    if name == \"risky_operation\":\n        if has_elicitation:\n            result = await ctx.session.elicit(\n                message=\"Confirm risky operation?\",\n                requestedSchema={\n                    \"type\": \"object\",\n                    \"properties\": {\n                        \"confirm\": {\"type\": \"boolean\", \"title\": \"Confirm\"}\n                    },\n                    \"required\": [\"confirm\"]\n                }\n            )\n            if result.action != \"accept\" or not result.content.get(\"confirm\"):\n                return [types.TextContent(type=\"text\", text=\"Operation cancelled.\")]\n        else:\n            # Fallback: refuse to proceed without confirmation\n            return [types.TextContent(\n                type=\"text\",\n                text=\"This operation requires user confirmation. \"\n                     \"Your host does not support elicitation. \"\n                     \"Use a host that supports interactive confirmation to run this tool.\"\n            )]\n\n        return [types.TextContent(type=\"text\", text=\"Operation completed.\")]\n\n    raise ValueError(f\"Unknown tool: {name}\")"
          }
        ]
      },
