            "type": "text",
            "text": "Elicitation lets MCP servers pause a tool call to collect input directly from the human operator, without injecting extra turns into the model conversation. The protocol uses elicitation/create with a JSON Schema form definition; the host renders a UI and returns the human's response as accept/decline/cancel. Servers check client capability before calling .elicit(), provide a fallback for hosts that don't support it, and always handle every response action gracefully."
